# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
#  Copy this file to .env and fill in every required value.
#  Never commit the real .env to version control.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── Telegram ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Bot token from @BotFather
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=1234567890:AAFxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# API credentials from https://my.telegram.org  (required by Pyrogram/MTProto)
TELEGRAM_API_ID=12345678
TELEGRAM_API_HASH=abcdef1234567890abcdef1234567890

# ── GitHub ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Personal Access Token with repo scope
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Repository coordinates
GITHUB_OWNER=your_username
GITHUB_REPO=your_repo_name
GITHUB_BRANCH=main                    # optional, default: main

# ── Upload behaviour ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
UPLOAD_BASE_PATH=uploads              # optional, default: uploads
FILE_CONFLICT_STRATEGY=version        # optional: "version" (default) or "overwrite"

# Files this size or larger (in MB) are stored via Git LFS instead of the
# Contents API (which has a 100 MB hard limit).
# Lower this value if you frequently upload files between 50–100 MB.
LFS_THRESHOLD_MB=50                   # optional, default: 50

# ── VPS disk cleanup ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When enabled, the bot deletes the oldest uploaded files from the repo once
# total size exceeds CLEANUP_MAX_REPO_MB.  Useful for small (10 GB) VPS disks.
CLEANUP_ENABLED=false                 # optional, default: false
CLEANUP_MAX_REPO_MB=800               # optional, default: 800  — trigger threshold (MB)
CLEANUP_KEEP_LATEST=10                # optional, default: 10   — newest files never deleted

# ── Access control ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Comma-separated Telegram user IDs that may use the bot.
# Leave empty to allow everyone.
ALLOWED_USER_IDS=123456789,987654321

# Telegram user ID that receives error reports. Leave empty to disable.
ADMIN_USER_ID=123456789

# ── Logging ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
LOG_LEVEL=INFO                        # optional: DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR
LOG_FILE=logs/bot.log                 # optional, default: logs/bot.log
